      },
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 standard condition (5 mm/min, 23°C, standard fixture). The standard test condition does not bracket the full range of in vivo loading rates or temperatures. This limitation is acknowledged; however, the ASTM F1717 condition is the regulatory-accepted surrogate for clinical loading, and sensitivity analysis (see hasSensitivityAnalysis) confirmed QoI variation < 4% across the plausible in vivo loading-rate range. Achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3; offset rationale documented in the decision record."
